Foot-and-mouth disease, Zimbabwe
--------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 16 May 2014 from Dr Unesu Hildah Ushewokunze-Obatolu, principal director, Division of Veterinary Field Services, Department of Livestock and Veterinary Services, Harare, Zimbabwe

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 14 April 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 1 May 2014
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: August 2013
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: SAT 1
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (3)
Outbreak 1: Alko ranch, Rutenga, Mwenezi, Masvingo
Date of start of the outbreak: 14 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 722 / 368 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: beef cattle of all ages under extensive production system

Outbreak 2: kayalami dip tank, Rutenga, Mwenezi, Masvingo
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1746 / 150 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: beef cattle of all ages under extensive production system

Outbreak 3: Fauna ranch, Rutenga, Mwenezi, Masvingo
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 672 / 105 / 7 / 0 / 0
Affected population: beef cattle of all ages under extensive production system with mortalities in calves.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3140 / 623 / 7 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 19.84 / 0.22 / 1.12 / 0.22
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: contact with infected animal(s) at grazing watering; contact with wild species
Epidemiological comments: all 3 outbreaks occurred in adjoining farms close to a wildlife conservancy with wild buffaloes. There was evidence of fence breakages on the conservancy perimeter fence, which may have resulted in mixing of cattle and buffaloes. Infection is likely to have spread from Alko ranch to Fauna and Kayalami through cattle to cattle contact.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of wildlife reservoirs; quarantine; movement control inside the country; zoning; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / Cattle / antibody detection ELISA / 6 May 2014 / Positive
Zimbabwe Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 1 May 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

